Return to Learn Plan

Butler County Health Department
July 30 at 3:08 PM ·

Over the past several months, Poplar Bluff educators have gathered best practices from schools across Missouri and the country and solicited input from local health care officials, parents, students, and other stakeholders. The information below is designed to help parents/guardians make informed decisions with regard to the learning experience of your child(ren) as we begin the 2020/21 school year with added safety measures in place to help mitigate risk for families during the pandemic.

https://www.poplarbluffschools.net/parent_resources/return_to_learn_plan

shared_text:
Poplar Bluff Early Childhood Center
May 27 at 6:15 PM ·

Are you interested in your child attending the Poplar Bluff Early Childhood program for the 2020-2021 school year? Our next screening will be held on June 16, 2020. If you have a child or know someone who would like to get their child into the Poplar Bluff Early Childhood program next year, please call 573-785-6803 for an appointment. A child must turn 3 by July 31, 2020, and be no older than 5 by July 31, 2020, to be eligible to attend. Also, please have your child's social security number handy when you call. This information is required to complete the appointment. This is for NEW/PROSPECTIVE students only.

PLEASE HELP UP US SHARE THIS INFORMATION! THANKS!

Are you interested in your child attending the Poplar Bluff Early Childhood Half Day program for the 2020-2021 school year? Our next screening will be held on March 10, 2020. If you have a child or know someone who would like to get their child into Poplar Bluff Early Childhood program next year, please call 573-785-6803 for an appointment. A child must turn 3 by July 31, 2020, and be no older than 5 by July 31, 2020, to be eligible to attend. Also, please have your child's social security number handy when you call. This information is required to complete the appointment. This is for NEW/PROSPECTIVE students only.

PLEASE HELP UP US SHARE THIS INFORMATION! THANKS!

October 7, 2019 at 5:56 PM ·

Lake Road Elementary is mourning the loss of our dear paw friend, Airial. She has succumbed to a long battle with cancer and is suffering no longer. She has provided so much love and support to our students and staff over her eight years of service. We will never forget her joyous, calm spirit. Please keep Mrs. Duncan’s family and our school family in your thoughts.

We are so excited about the progress at the Poplar Bluff Early Childhood Center. The strategically placed color in the halls at the classroom entrances create township communities for ease of wayfinding for the little ones. The open skylight by way of the cupola in the lobby provides clear natural light as the families enter. The Early Childhood Center is located next to the existing Kindergarten Center. We are pleased to collaborate with some partners on this project. Poplar Bluff Schools, VVELL Studio, Brockmiller Construction Incorporated, Smith & Co. Engineers, Case Engineering, Inc., @Smith & Boucher Engineers.

Congratulations Oak Grove Elementary for receiving the “Gold Star” award from the MO Department of Education. This prestigious award is only given to 8 schools throughout Missouri. It was an honor to present a Senate Resolution to the many teachers who were in attendance to accept the resolution recognizing this amazing achievement of their students, staff and parents.

Recipients of the state’s award are nominated for the National Blue Ribbon recognition. Good luck on the national “Blue Ribbon” entry.

PBJHS
August 7, 2019 at 11:46 PM ·

APPRECIATION POST❤️❤️
Jill Evans, Regional Director with Maco Management, donated backpacks to Poplar Bluff JR High. Poplar Bluff Villas sponsored the backpacks as part of their back to school bash that was given to the residents last week. The back to school bash provided dinner for the families, playing water games outside with all of the residents and having tons of fun! Poplar Bluff Villas then gave every student there a new backpack filled with supplies needed to start school and wanted to keep paying it forward.
The Poplar Bluff Villas is a newly constructed 48 unit community located at 2301 Eugene Blvd in Poplar Bluff. Meredith Wiggins, District Manager for our Poplar Bluff and surrounding areas, takes much pride in her properties and couldn’t be prouder to have one of many of her properties pay it forward to PB residents and the school community.
#pbcommunity

Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
June 17, 2019 at 2:15 PM ·

The Department of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) has named this year’s Missouri Gold Star Schools. The program recognizes schools that perform at high academic levels or that perform at high levels while serving a significant proportion of disadvantaged students.

Congratulations to Poplar Bluff Schools, Francis Howell School District, Kirkwood School District, Blue Springs School District, Ladue School District and Hickory County R-1 School District Skyline districts/schools for being selected this year!

Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education
June 17, 2019 at 2:15 PM ·

The Department of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) has named this year’s Missouri Gold Star Schools. The program recognizes schools that perform at high academic levels or that perform at high levels while serving a significant proportion of disadvantaged students.

Congratulations to Poplar Bluff Schools, Francis Howell School District, Kirkwood School District, Blue Springs School District, Ladue School District and Hickory County R-1 School District Skyline districts/schools for being selected this year!

https://dese.mo.gov/communications/news-releases/missouri-announces-2019-gold-star-schools
